Ad Text:
Hobart based candidates only
Energy and Utilities sector
Cyber resilience, end-user computing and business continuity experience required
A large Energy and Utilities company is seeking 3 experienced IT Business Analysts to support the delivery of critical enterprise IT initiatives across cyber resilience, end-user computing and business continuity.

This role suits Business Analysts who are highly structured, detail-oriented and experienced in requirements management, process analysis and stakeholder engagement within complex IT environments.

Responsibilities:

Planning and leading business analysis activities across IT projects
Facilitating workshops and interviews to elicit, validate and prioritise requirements
Documenting current-state and future-state processes, business rules and dependencies
Managing requirements traceability and change governance (RTM)
Supporting options analysis, business cases and solution evaluation
Assisting with procurement evaluation, testing support and benefits realisation
Projects you may support:
CyberVault and enterprise backup platforms
Azure Virtual Desktop (AVD) and VDI modernisation
OS hardening and CIS benchmarking initiatives
Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery (BIA/DRP) uplift programs
Essential Criteria:
5+ years’ experience as an IT Business Analyst
Strong experience in:

Requirements elicitation and documentation
Process mapping and analysis
Stakeholder engagement across business and technical teams
Experience supporting infrastructure, cyber or EUC projects
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
Comfortable working in structured, governance-driven environments
How to Apply

If you're ready to take on the next challenge in your career and you think you can bring your passion to this exciting role, then please click on 'Apply Now' to submit your cover letter and resume. For specific questions relating to the role please contract Nick at nraicevich@genesisit.com.au.

Diversity and inclusion are strongly supported at Genesis IT Recruitment. People of all nationalities, gender identities, and cultural backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, are encouraged to apply.

Job Title: General Manager, Policy and Analysis Branch, Net Zero Economy Authority
Company: Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet
Ad Text:
Step into a pivotal leadership role as General Manager, Policy and Analysis with the Net Zero Economy Authority, where you’ll drive national policy and data strategy at the forefront of Australia’s economic and social transformation. This is your opportunity to shape the Authority’s policy agenda, lead high-performing teams, and deliver evidence-based insights that support workers, communities, and industries through the net zero transition. You’ll collaborate with senior officials, industry, and regional leaders, ensuring decisions are informed by robust analysis and innovative thinking. If you’re a strategic, values-driven leader with a passion for public sector impact and a commitment to building a better future, this high-profile executive position offers the chance to make a lasting difference.

Flexibility arrangements

Flexible work is a broad term used to describe a variety of different arrangements about how, when and where work is performed. The authority supports mutually beneficial flexible work arrangements which suit operational requirements. Arrangements may be consistent and regular, such as part time work, working from home a couple of days each week or remotely from another location; or more ad hoc such as varying work attendance times or occasional home based work. Consideration is given to all flexible work requests, approval is not limited to an employee’s classification level or caring responsibilities.

Eligibility

This role is being advertised as both ongoing and non-ongoing. The role may be offered as either ongoing or non-ongoing subject to business needs and/or candidate preference. Where a non-ongoing position is offered, the role will be filled as a specified term vacancy for an initial period of up to 12 months.
Under section 22(8) of the Public Service Act 1999, employees must be Australian citizens to be employed in the Australian Public Service (APS) unless the Agency Head has agreed otherwise, in writing. At NZEA (PM&C) to be eligible for this position you should be an Australian Citizen at the closing date of application, unless exceptional circumstances apply (see FAQs in the candidate information pack for more details).
Successful applicants will be required to undergo the process to obtain and maintain, or continue to hold the required security clearance level for the role as indicated. All NZEA staff are required to have a minimum baseline security clearance prior to commencement.
Successful applicants will be assessed through our pre-employment screening checks, including a Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check, and will normally be subject to a six-month probation period if new to the APS, or if they have not yet completed their probation period elsewhere in the APS.

How to apply

If this sounds like the opportunity you are looking for, submit an online application through the Apply link by Sunday, 18 January 2026 at 11:30pm AEDT.

Senior Financial Analyst - 6-Month Contract

Location: Artarmon, NSW

Work Arrangement: Hybrid

Contract:Temporary (6 months)

Your new company
Join a global leader in the industrial sector that is committed to innovation and excellence. This organisation offers a collaborative environment and the flexibility of hybrid working.

Your new role
As a Senior Financial Analyst, you will provide critical financial insights and analysis to support strategic decision-making. This is a 6-month temporary contract where you will work closely with senior stakeholders and contribute to key projects.


Key responsibilities include:

Preparing and analysing financial reports to support business performance
Monthly balance sheet reconciliations
Conducting variance analysis and identifying key trends
Assisting with budgeting, forecasting, and month-end processes
Supporting strategic initiatives and providing financial modelling
Collaborating with cross-functional teams to deliver accurate and timely insights

What you'll need to succeed

CA/CPA or equivalent
Must be immediately available
3-5 years of commercial experience post qualification
SAP experience preferred
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Advanced Excel and financial modelling capabilities
Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills

What you'll get in return

Competitive daily rate
Hybrid working arrangement
Opportunity to work with a global leader in the industrial sector
Exposure to strategic projects and senior leadership

New year, new opportunity to grow your career in a dynamic and supportive multinational with excellent career progression!

About your new Employer!
  
This multinational, product-based organisation is a leader in its category across the APAC region. With strong year-on-year growth, complex operations and a genuinely collaborative culture, the business is investing heavily in commercial finance capability to support strategic decision-making. You’ll join a high-performing finance team that values curiosity, continuous improvement, and evidence-based insight. This is an environment where your recommendations influence senior leadership and directly shape future business outcomes.
  
About your new Role!
  
We’re looking for an experienced Finance Business Partner to step into a highly analytical, commercially impactful role with APAC-wide scope. Reporting directly to the CFO, you’ll work alongside multiple Finance Business Partners and will be the one who brings it all together. Your mandate is to take large volumes of operational and commercial data, analyse it, interpret it, and convert it into clear, actionable insights that support strategic and operational decision-making.
  
This role exists because the CFO needs more than just data, he needs meaningful stories, informed recommendations, and an ability to provide insights that influence business outcomes.
  
Key responsibilities include:

Business partnering across sales, operations, logistics and commercial teams
Analysing large datasets and distilling insights to support decision-making
Leading and coordinating the full planning process across APAC
Assessing the quality and reliability of sales forecasts and market assumptions
Supporting Sales & Operations Planning (S&OP) with commercial insight
CAPEX analysis, evaluation and recommendations
Identifying performance improvement opportunities and providing strategic suggestions
Storytelling: presenting insights in a compelling, logical, and impactful way
  
About You!

Professional qualification such as CA, CPA, CFA is desirable but not essential
3-5 years experience in a commercial role such as Finance Business Partner, Commercial Analyst, Commercial Manager
Highly analytical capability with experience working across large, complex datasets
Proven ability to convert numbers into commercial stories, insights and recommendations
Product based industry experience such as FMCG, Consumer Goods,  Manufacturing or similar is highly desirable
Strong understanding of planning cycles, forecasting and long-term modelling
Demonstrated ability to influence senior stakeholders and guide others through the planning process
Curious, commercially minded and proactive; constantly questioning how performance can be improved
Exceptional communication and stakeholder engagement skills
  
What’s in it for You?

Circa. $160,000 – $175,000 base + super + bonus
High-impact role with direct influence on APAC strategy
Work closely with a commercial, forward-thinking CFO
Clear and tangible career progression opportunities
Collaborative culture with strong executive exposure
Hybrid working arrangement | Close to Public Transport
Please APPLY NOW or contact Declan Stacey on 0483 945 773 for more information.

Binance is a leading global blockchain ecosystem behind the world’s largest cryptocurrency exchange by trading volume and registered users. We are trusted by over 280 million people in 100+ countries for our industry-leading security, user fund transparency, trading engine speed, deep liquidity, and an unmatched portfolio of digital-asset products. Binance offerings range from trading and finance to education, research, payments, institutional services, Web3 features, and more. We leverage the power of digital assets and blockchain to build an inclusive financial ecosystem to advance the freedom of money and improve financial access for people around the world.

We are looking for a Data Scientist expert to drive advancements in natural language processing and computer vision. You’ll work across content understanding scenarios such as classification, entity recognition, sentiment analysis, and image/video understanding, and help build large-scale systems that power content moderation, recommendation, and search.

Develop and optimize NLP/CV algorithms to improve the performance and efficiency of content understanding pipelines.
Build scalable models (e.g., BERT, GPT, ViT, CLIP) and bring them into production.
Partner with product and data teams to diagnose business challenges and design data-driven solutions.
Track cutting-edge research and explore novel algorithms for real-world applications in content understanding.
Drive system improvements that enhance moderation, recommendation and search workflow
Master’s Degree or above in Computer Science, AI, EE, Mathematics, or related fields.
Strong programming skills in Python or C++ and familiarity with deep learning frameworks such as PyTorch.
Solid foundation in machine learning/deep learning and hands-on experience with common models in NLP and/or CV.
Experience working with large-scale data processing frameworks (Hadoop/Spark/Flink is a plus).
2+ years of algorithm/model development experience.
Background in content safety, recommendation or search systems is highly valued.

Why Binance

• Shape the future with the world’s leading blockchain ecosystem

• Collaborate with world-class talent in a user-centric global organization with a flat structure

• Tackle unique, fast-paced projects with autonomy in an innovative environment

• Thrive in a results-driven workplace with opportunities for career growth and continuous learning

• Competitive salary and company benefits

• Work-from-home arrangement (the arrangement may vary depending on the work nature of the business team)
